ieto, G., Takashima, K., Katsura, S., Mizuno, A., Performance evaluation of discharge plasma process for gaseous pollutant removal (2002) J. Electrostat., 55 (1), pp. 25-41; Chae, J.O., Non-thermal plasma for diesel exhaust treatment (2003) J. Electrostat., 57 (3-4), pp. 251-262; Cardello, N., Volckens, J., Tolocka, M.P., Wiener, R., Buckley, T.J., Technical note: Performance of a personal electrostatic precipitator particle sampler (2002) Aerosol. Sci. Technol., 36 (2), pp. 162-165; Chen, J.H., Davidson, J.H., Model of the negative DC corona plasma: Comparison to the positive DC corona plasma (2003) Plasma Chem. Plasma Process, 23 (1), pp. 83-102; Chen, J.H., Davidson, J.H., Ozone production in the negative DC corona: The dependence of discharge polarity (2003) Plasma Chem. Plasma Process., 23 (3), pp. 501-518; Hueglin, C., Scherrer, L., Burtscher, H., An accurate, continuously adjustable dilution system (1:10 to 1:104) for submicron aerosols (1997) J. Aerosol. Sci., 28 (6), pp. 1049-1055; Gobrecht, H., (1974) Bergmann, Schäfer - Lehrbuch Der Experimentalphysik, 1. , (Ed.), de Gruyter; Beitz, W.a.K., Beitz, K.-H., Dubbel - Taschenbuch für den Maschinenbau (1981), (Ed.) Springer, BerlinTownsend, J.S., (1915) Philos. Mag., 28 (83); Sigmond, R.S., Simple approximate treatment of unipolar space-charge-dominated coronas - The Warburg law and the saturation current (1982) J. Appl. Phys., 53 (2), pp. 891-898; Jones, J.E., Boullod, A., Waters, R.T., Dimensonal analysis of corona discharges: The small current regime for rod-plane geometry in air (1990) J. Phys. D, 23, pp. 1652-1662; Carreno, F., Bernabeu, E., On wire-to-plane positive corona discharge (1994) J. Phys. D, 27, pp. 2136-2144; Morrow, R., The theory of positive glow corona (1997) J. Phys. D, 30, pp. 3099-3114; Ferreira, G.F.L., Oliveira, O.N., Giacometti, J.A., Point-to-plane corona - Current-voltage characteristics for positive and negative polarity with evidence of an electronic- component (1986) J. Appl. Phys